Package BrowserSystem

  • Interface Summary
    Interface Description
    BrowseState
    BrowseState is the interface for which all of the states implement in the subsystem.
  • Class Summary
    Class Description
    ArtistState
    ArtistState represents the state in the browsing system where a user has selected an artist to explore.
    Browser
    Browser represents an instance where the user is looking to browse their personal collection.
    CollectionState
    CollectionState is the state where the user has called the initial browse command, in this state, all of the artists in the user's library.
    DefaultState
    DefaultState is the state of the browser before a browse command is called.
    ReleaseState
    ReleaseState is the lowest level in the browse searching tree.
